(Before the anthem plays, please stand for the pride of our nation.)

National Heroes of India(Freedom Fighter)

Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose

Leader of Azad Hind Fauj

A fearless leader who inspired millions to join the fight for India’s independence. Known for his slogan "Give me blood, and I shall give you freedom."

Bhagat Singh

Revolutionary Freedom Fighter

A fearless young revolutionary who fought against British colonial rule and embraced martyrdom at the age of 23 to awaken the spirit of independence.

Mangal Pandey

First Martyr of 1857 Revolt

Known as the spark of the First War of Independence in 1857, he sacrificed his life fighting against the injustices of the British East India Company.

Chandra Shekhar Azad

Revolutionary Leader

A bold revolutionary who vowed never to be captured alive by the British and kept his promise till his last breath in 1931.

Rani Lakshmibai

Queen of Jhansi

The warrior queen who fought valiantly against the British in 1857, symbolizing courage, resistance, and sacrifice.

Matangini Hazra

Freedom Fighter

An unarmed protester shot dead while leading a procession against British rule in 1942, chanting “Vande Mataram” till her last breath.

Tantia Tope

1857 Revolt General

A brilliant military leader of the 1857 revolt, known for his guerrilla warfare tactics and ultimate sacrifice for the motherland.

Indian Defence Heroes

Honoring the brave soldiers of the Indian Army, Navy, and Air Force who have dedicated their lives to protect our motherland.

Captain Vikram Batra

Param Vir Chakra, Kargil War 1999

Known as the "Sher Shah" of Kargil, Captain Vikram Batra led his troops to victory at Point 4875, showing unmatched courage and patriotism.

Captain Mahendra Nath Mulla

Maha Vir Chakra, 1971 Indo-Pak War

Commanding officer of INS Khukri who chose to go down with his ship during the 1971 war, inspiring generations of naval officers.

Flying Officer Nirmal Jit Singh Sekhon

Param Vir Chakra, 1971 Indo-Pak War

The only IAF officer to receive the Param Vir Chakra, he fearlessly fought Pakistani Sabre jets during the 1971 war, protecting Srinagar air base.

CQMH Abdul Hamid

Param Vir Chakra (Posthumous) – 1965 War

Famous for destroying enemy tanks in the 1965 Indo-Pak war, he is remembered as a tank-buster hero who showed extreme valor in the face of heavy fire.

Lamp of Love

Admiral S.M. Nanda

Operation Trident – 1971 War

As Chief of Naval Staff, he led the Navy during the 1971 war, masterminding Operation Trident and Operation Python that crippled the Pakistani Navy.

Arjan Singh

Marshal of the Air Force

The only officer to hold the five-star rank in the Indian Air Force. Played a crucial role in the 1965 war, inspiring generations of air warriors.

Selfless Spirit
